THE STUDENT PILOT REPORTED THAT THE LT MAIN WHEEL ROLLED OFF THE RUNWAY 
INTO MUD DURING LDG ROLLOUT. THIS PULLED THE AIRCRAFT OFF THE RUNWAY AND 
DOWN AN EMBANKMENT INTO A DITCH. THE NOSE GEAR SUBSEQUENTLY SANK 
INTO THE MUD AND THE AIRCRAFT NOSED DOWN. THE AIRCRAFT CAME TO REST ON THE 
NOSE AND RIGHT WING. THE STUDENT PILOT REPORIGHTED THAT THIS WAS HIS SECOND 
SOLO FLIGHT. 
